Package com.cafean.client.values.components

Class NumericsTableColumn

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.values.components.NumericsTableColumn
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloneableBlock, Checkable, ComponentElement, IdentHolder, ModelElement, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    public class NumericsTableColumn
extends java.lang.Object
implements Checkable, CloneableBlock, ComponentElement, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable, IdentHolder
    This class provides IO access to NumericsTableColumn data bocks. This class properly handles instantiating CReals to the correct subclass, so long as the provided CReal base and/or array are of the desired type.

      • NumericsTableColumn

        public NumericsTableColumn​(java.lang.String name,
                           java.lang.String desc,
                           ComponentElement owner,
                           CReal[] values,
                           CReal realClass)
        Creates a new NumericsTableColumn instance with the given values. The type of the new column is automatically set to TYPE_REAL.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the column; this value may contain HTML if wrapped with the text "<html><body>" and "</html></body>"
        desc - a short description of the column; the description can specify a title by specifying it within square-brackets at the beginning of the string
        owner - the owner of the new NumericsTableColumn
        values - the array to display in this column: note that this method directly uses this array; it does not create a clone of the array or any of its elements. Furthermore, the array contained in this column will may not be the same array after the column has been edited, and will absolutely not be the same array if the column is resized
        realClass - an instance of a CReal extension used to instantiate new reals and real arrays
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any of name, desc, or values are null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if realClass does not indicate a subclass of CReal

      • reconnectIdentReferences

        public void reconnectIdentReferences​(boolean preserveUnresolved,
                                     boolean useDbId)
        Description copied from interface: IdentHolder
        Resets this component's internal ident references to refer to appropriate components in the current AbstractModel. Intended for use after adding a component to a model and thus it's DB_ID will have been set to it's ident in the previous model. For ident references use find__ByDbId to find the new component, then store it's ident.

        Note: If this component's DB_ID is 0 this method does nothing.

        Specified by:
        reconnectIdentReferences in interface IdentHolder
        Parameters:
        preserveUnresolved - if true, ident references that aren't resolvable will be left dangling, if false, they will be set to 0.
        useDbId - if true, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByDB_ID; if false, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByIdent
